:{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to rise, to get up","examples":[{"text":"أَنْهَضُ مِنَ النَّوْمِ كُلَّ صَبَاحٍ بَاكِرًا.","english":"I get up early every morning."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"awakening, rise"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Morphologically from the root ن ه ض (n h ḍ)."},"ipa":["/na.ha.dˤa/","/nahdˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40660","headword_ar":"نَهَضَ","root":"nhD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuhuwDN","text_ar":"نُهُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahoDN","text_ar":"نَهْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stood up."},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirotafaEa","text_ar":"اِرْتَفَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAma","text_ar":"قَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano makaAnihi","text_ar":"عَنْ مَكَانِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from his place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnthD","text_ar":"انتهض","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAma","text_ar":"قَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAar:) or the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he quitted a place:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he rose from it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he rose from sitting;"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus differing from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahada","text_ar":"نَهَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which signifies “ he rose ” under any circumstances: (M, L, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nhd","text_ar":"نهد"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he rose and went:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he rose and hastened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as shown below:] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnthD","text_ar":"انتهض","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excited, to rise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stand up;"},{"kind":"text","text":"quasipass. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anohaDahu","text_ar":"اَنْهَضَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahaDa A_ilayohi","text_ar":"نَهَضَ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stood up, to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA^amorK","text_ar":"لِاَمْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to do,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perform, an affair"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K. *) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahaDa A_ilaY AlEaduw~i","text_ar":"نَهَضَ اـِلَى العَدُوِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hastened. to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards, the enemy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahada","text_ar":"نَهَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahaDonaA A_ilaY Alqawomi","text_ar":"نَهَضْنَا اـِلَى القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nagaDonaA A_ilayohimo","text_ar":"نَغَضْنَا اـِلَيْهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We rose and sped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hastened, to."},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards, the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company of men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] both signify the same. (Abu-l-Jahm El-Jaafaree.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnthDwA","text_ar":"انتهضوا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tnAhDwA","text_ar":"تناهضوا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahaDuwA liloqitaAli","text_ar":"نَهَضُوا لِلْقِتَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They rose and sped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hastened, to fight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the fight"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a plant)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stood erect;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became strong and erect."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K.) ―         -b3-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a bird)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spread,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expanded, its wings to fly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroxN EaAjizu Aln~uhoD","text_ar":"فَرْخٌ عَاجِزُ النُّهْض"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A young bird lacking the power of spreading its wings to fly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) [See an ex. in a verse of El- Hoteíäh cited in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xlf","text_ar":"خلف"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahaDato nafosuhu","text_ar":"نَهَضَتْ نَفْسُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j$A^","text_ar":"جشا"},{"kind":"text","text":". &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahaDato","text_ar":"نَهَضَتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafosuhu A_ilayohi","text_ar":"نَفْسُهُ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in the same art, and A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jh$","text_ar":"جهش"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.) signify [the same. i. e.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ja$A^ato","text_ar":"جَشاَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His said,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stomach, heaved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] (S, A, K. in the arts. above mentioned.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahaDa Al$~ayobu fiY Al$~abaAbi","text_ar":"نَهَضَ الشَّيْبُ فِى الشَّبَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hoariness a rose in youth"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (A, TA.) As cites the following verse from an anonymous poet:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"Alor~iEodapu fiY ZuhayoriY ↓ \n      tanotahiDu\n                      \n                     \n                        mino laduni AlZ~uhori A_ilaY AlEuSayori"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tremor arises in my little back from the time of noon to the little evening."},{"kind":"text","text":"). (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","Msb","K","O","IAar","M","TA"]}]}}